For years, the Road Accident Fund has struggled with its finances and its administration. The RAF has a debt of over R300 billion. Transport Minister, Fikile Mbalula has said the dispensation of the fund is not sustainable. * Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - For years, the Road Accident Fund (RAF) has struggled with its finances and its administration. The RAF has a debt of over R300-billion. READ: RAF's R300bn debt and other issues Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula has said the dispensation of the fund is not sustainable. Mbalula is talking about what measures are being taken to stabilise the entity.